{
  "texts": [
    "When using LLMs as an autocomplete engine, i.e., without chat templates, we found a large increase in toxic stereotyping across models.",
    "We discuss implications for model builders, NLP practitioners and policy makers (Birhane et al. 2024) in Section 5.",
    "This section focuses on moderation practices during LLM development (§2.1), evaluation of harms post development (§2.2), and stereotyping in search engine autocompletion and generative AI, including the stakes (§2.3).",
    "For Llama-2, 'safety training' is focused on 'illicit and criminal activities', 'hateful and harmful activities' and 'unqualified advice' (Touvron et al. 2023).",
    "The authors conduct fine-tuning, Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF; Christiano et al. 2017) and context distillation (Askell et al. 2021)."
  ]
}